aĝ: age (how old someone or something is)
animal: animal (as opposed to vegetable or mineral)
deviz: rallying cry; draft on foreign bank
iks: the name of the letter X
moŝt: (general title for persons of high rank)
obol: obolus (a Greek silver coin worth a sixth of a drachma)

akuŝ: be in the process of giving birth
brokant: to buy and sell used (second-hand) products
entrepren: to undertake (take it upon oneself to do)
komplez: to be so kind as to
konstat: to ascertain to be true (a fact)
kontrakt: to enter into a contract with

ad: (denotes continuation or constant repetition of an action)
aĵ: (denotes something possessing a certain quality or made from a certain substance, meat from a specific animal)
ant: ending of pres. part. act. in verbs
ar: (denotes a collection of persons or objects)
at: ending of pres. part. pass. in verbs
ĉj: (used to form diminutives with masculine names)
ej: (place used for an action or object)
end: (denotes something to be done or which must be done)
ig: (denotes causing or bringing about an state, creates causative verbs, to make, render)
iĝ: (denotes that a state has come into being, become)
il: (denotes the instrument by which something is done)
ing: (denotes a holder for the object contained in the root)
int: ending of past part. act. in verbs
ist: (denotes one who occupies oneself with something)
it: ending of past part. pass. in verbs
nj: (used to form diminutives with feminine names)
ont: ending of fut. part. act. in verbs
ot: ending of fut. part. pass. in verbs
uj: (denotes a container, country formed from the name of its people, tree formed from name of its fruit)
um: (denotes some undefined action or object related to the root)
kelk: (denotes addition of an undefined but small number)
(denotes multiplication by an undefined but small number)
(sometimes used with the meaning of "about" or "some")
ek: (denotes an action which begins or is of short duration)
mal: (prefix used to form word of opposite meaning)

do: therefore; name of the letter D
mem: (puts emphasis on the noun or pronoun it follows)
